Set aside 2 TBSP @garlic herb butter{3.5%oz} to soften to room temperature.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Toss @baby carrots{1%pound} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast carrots on top rack ~{18-22%minutes}, or until softened.

Remove baking sheet from oven. Toss carrots with softened garlic herb butter and @Mike's Hot Honey{2.25%oz} to taste.

> Chop equal parts chives and parsley. Toss your sweet-and-savory glazed carrots with the herbs, softened garlic herb butter, and hot honey to taste.